<b><big><a name="Description">Description</a></big></b>
<br/>
Returns an
<code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>AD&lt;</span></font></code><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>Base</span></i><code><font color="blue"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>&gt;</span></font></code> object specified by

<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><mrow>
<mrow><mstyle mathvariant='normal'><mi mathvariant='normal'>pow</mi>
</mstyle></mrow>
<mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">,</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
<mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
<msup><mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
</msup>
</mrow></math>

If <i>y</i> is an <code><font color="blue">int</font></code>, the calculation is performed using
repeated multiplications.
Otherwise the <a href="log.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>log</span></a>
 of <i>y</i> must be defined.
(for example, if <i>y</i> is zero, its log is not defined).


<br/>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Assumptions">Assumptions</a></big></b>
<br/>
If <i>y</i> is not an <code><font color="blue">int</font></code>,
the derivative assumptions for the 
<a href="log.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>log</span></a>
 and <a href="exp.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>exp</span></a>
 functions must hold.

<br/>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Standard Base Types">Standard Base Types</a></big></b>
<br/>
A definition for the <code><font color="blue">pow</font></code> function
is automatically included (in the <code><font color="blue">CppAD</font></code> namespace)
for the following 
<a href="glossary_frame1.xml#Base Type" target="frame1"><i><span style='white-space: nowrap'>base&#xA0;types</span></i></a>
:
<code><font color="blue">float</font></code>, <code><font color="blue">double</font></code>, <code><font color="blue">complex&lt;float&gt;</font></code>, 
and <code><font color="blue">complex&lt;double&gt;</font></code>.


<br/>
<br/>
<b><big><a name="Example">Example</a></big></b>

<br/>
The file
<a href="powint.cpp.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>PowInt.cpp</span></a>

contains an example and test of this function for the case
where <i>y</i> is an <code><font color="blue">int</font></code>.   
The file
<a href="pow.cpp.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>Pow.cpp</span></a>

contains an example and test of this function for the case
where <i>y</i> is not an <code><font color="blue">int</font></code>.   
Both tests return true if they succeed and false otherwise.


